    "India ranks 3rd globally in greenhouse gas emissions, accounting for ~7.0% of world CO2e (2024)",
    "Total emissions rose 9.2% from 3.89 Bt (2022) to 4.25 Bt CO2e (2024)",
    "Power generation (coal) remains the largest sector at 1.45 Bt CO2e — 34% of India's total",
    "Agriculture is the 2nd largest sector at 898 Mt CO2e (21%) — cattle and rice dominate",
    "Manufacturing accounts for 792 Mt CO2e (19%) — steel and cement are the main contributors",
    "Buildings sector (324 Mt) and transportation (270 Mt) each represent 6-8% of emissions",
    "Fossil fuel operations contribute 264 Mt CO2e from coal mining, oil & gas refining and production",
    "The top 10 coal power plants alone emit 229 Mt CO2e — equivalent to the entire emissions of many countries",
    "NTPC Ltd operates 5 of India's 10 most polluting power plants (Vindhyachal, Rihand, Talcher, Korba, Sipat)",
